msgid "Title: YunoHost DNS Resolver"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/dns_resolver.md:5
msgid ""
"### Presentation YunoHost provide a DNS service for DNS name "
"resolution. Usually, your server is not configured to use it, it's your ISP "
"DNS. For instance, for the Free ISP with Freebox router the DNS resolver IP "
"is `192.168.0.254`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/dns_resolver.md:8
msgid ""
"How to known: watch the file `/etc/resolv.conf`. This file is not modifiable "
"because it is rewriten by the DHCP service. A DHCP client is configured, it "
"requests the router to get DNS resolver IPs.  This IPs is provided by your "
"ISP."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/dns_resolver.md:11
msgid ""
"### Configuration To use YunoHost DNS resolver of your server, modify your "
"DHCP configuration client: remove DNS name server request, and add static IP "
"of your server `127.0.0.1`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/dns_resolver.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Edit the file `/etc/dhcp/dhclient.conf`, add the line `supersede` and remove "
"in the line `request` the word `domain-name-servers`:\n"
"```bash\n"
"supersede domain-name-servers 127.0.0.1, 192.168.0.254;\n"
"request subnet-mask, broadcast-address, time-offset, routers,\n"
"        domain-name, domain-search, host-name,\n"
"        dhcp6.name-servers, dhcp6.domain-search,\n"
"        netbios-name-servers, netbios-scope, interface-mtu,\n"
"        rfc3442-classless-static-routes, ntp-servers;\n"
"```\n"
"Apply this modification by rebooting the server.\n"
msgstr ""

